main event: A civilian in Terre Haute, Indiana reported observing a bright, unidentified object in the sky on September 3, 1966.
interesting points: The object appeared to be as bright as a star and was observed for about 8 minutes.
The witness initially thought the object was a star, but noticed it had a 'definite brilliance' compared to other celestial bodies.
The object faded and disappeared from view over a 5-second period.
The witness sent a report to Project Blue Book, the U.S. Air Force program to investigate UFOs.
The Air Force responded, thanking the witness for the report and indicating they had not received any other sightings from the Terre Haute area on that night.
sighted object: a bright, unidentified object in the sky
